  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper. Cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the hazelnuts and cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.",
    "Add the chicken broth, honey, and lemon juice. Stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley or cilantro, if desired.",
    "Refrigerate or freeze any leftovers for up to 3 days."
